-Yeah. Hi, Min.

18:30.025 --> 18:31.777
No. We're… we're on our way.

18:32.528 --> 18:35.405
Great. I'm looking forward to meeting her.

18:35.489 --> 18:37.116
-Who?
-Martin's mother just arrived.

18:37.699 --> 18:39.701
Should we stop and get a bottle of wine?

18:40.994 --> 18:43.580
-What? That's terrible.
-What happened?

18:43.664 --> 18:45.541
No. No, that's not right.

18:45.624 --> 18:47.376
-What's not right?
-Hold on.

18:47.459 --> 18:51.088
Martin's mother made a joke
about Mindy's weight.

18:51.171 --> 18:53.924
-What kind of joke?
-Is there a good kind?

18:54.508 --> 18:57.469
Honey, listen. She's a stupid old woman.

18:57.553 --> 18:58.762
Just ignore her.

18:59.638 --> 19:02.391
-Ah, damn. Asshole.
-What asshole?

19:02.474 --> 19:03.934
No. You're right.

19:04.601 --> 19:07.187
He has to defend you.
Otherwise, what good is he?

19:07.271 --> 19:08.438
Is this Martin?

19:08.939 --> 19:11.024
He said nothing.
He just giggled like a little boy.

19:11.108 --> 19:13.443
All right. Listen-- No.

19:13.527 --> 19:17.156
Wait.
Don't you think that's a little extreme?

19:18.740 --> 19:21.368
Yeah. All right. I'll ask.

19:22.828 --> 19:26.039
She's really upset,
and she doesn't want to stay there.

19:26.123 --> 19:27.916
Of course. She doesn't have to ask.

19:28.709 --> 19:31.712
-He says of course.
-Wait, wait, wait. Well, what about you?

19:31.795 --> 19:33.172
What you do mean, "What about me?"

19:33.255 --> 19:35.174
I'm not staying
with Martin and his mother.

19:35.257 --> 19:36.592
Right. Yeah. You're right.

19:36.675 --> 19:39.136
She says thank you.
Honey, do me a favor.

19:39.219 --> 19:42.764
Throw all my stuff in the suitcase
and, uh, bring it with you, okay?

19:42.848 --> 19:44.266
Yeah. We'll meet you there.

19:44.349 --> 19:47.352
And, sweetheart, don't worry.

19:48.020 --> 19:49.438
This will all work out.

19:50.022 --> 19:50.939
I love you too.

19:51.815 --> 19:52.858
-Bye.
-[phone beeps]

19:55.819 --> 19:57.613
-Well, shit.
-Yeah.

19:59.323 --> 20:01.658
You know, I just have the two bedrooms.

20:02.284 --> 20:03.911
-You got a couch?
-Yeah.

20:04.786 --> 20:06.121
Then you'll be fine.

20:09.333 --> 20:11.543
I don't blame her. She's not the problem.

20:11.627 --> 20:14.046
She's just an evil, old, brain-dead cunt.

20:14.129 --> 20:14.963
It's him.

20:15.047 --> 20:17.841
He doesn't have the balls
to stand up to her!

20:17.925 --> 20:20.010
Some honey for my honey?

20:23.222 --> 20:26.058
I'm just glad this happened now
before the wedding.

20:26.141 --> 20:29.228
Otherwise, I'd be shackled
to that mama's boy for life.

20:34.024 --> 20:34.858
Yes.

20:35.359 --> 20:37.069
Martin should have said something,

20:37.152 --> 20:39.571
but that doesn't mean he's not a good guy.

20:39.655 --> 20:42.115
He's just trying
to be respectful of his mom.

20:42.199 --> 20:43.200
[Mindy] Fuck him!

20:43.283 --> 20:47.537
The whole time she was picking me apart,
he was looking down at his shoes.

20:47.621 --> 20:51.250
Stupid, ugly homemade shoes.

20:52.000 --> 20:53.293
You got anything stronger?

20:53.877 --> 20:55.796
-Uh, bourbon?
-Bring it!

20:56.964 --> 20:58.632
I don't care how old she is.

20:58.715 --> 21:00.550
I don't take that shit from anybody.

21:00.634 --> 21:01.677
Nor should you.

21:01.760 --> 21:05.847
The last person who talked to me like that
is still looking for his left nut.

21:05.931 --> 21:07.474
[Roz] Oh my. Um…

21:07.557 --> 21:11.061
You know, I think it would be a good idea
if we all got a good night's sleep

21:11.144 --> 21:12.896
and revisit this in the morning.

21:12.980 --> 21:14.731
There's nothing to revisit.

21:14.815 --> 21:17.192
The wedding's off. Good night.

21:19.403 --> 21:20.362
[exhales]

21:20.445 --> 21:21.530
Sweet dreams.

21:22.739 --> 21:23.573
Really?

21:24.366 --> 21:25.200
[sighs]

21:31.290 --> 21:34.209
-[car door slams]
-[Sandy grunts] I got a five a.m. call.

21:34.293 --> 21:35.585
Look what I'm doing.

21:37.170 --> 21:38.005
[spits]

21:38.755 --> 21:39.631
[banging on door]

21:40.299 --> 21:43.302
-What the hell? You'll wake her up.
-Ask me if I give a shit.

21:43.385 --> 21:46.722
You need to go to my house,
get down on your knees

21:46.805 --> 21:48.849
and beg Mindy to forgive you.

21:48.932 --> 21:50.517
Okay. It's… it's a little late.

21:50.600 --> 21:53.228
Can I beg first thing in the morning
when I'm fresh?

21:53.312 --> 21:56.732
-[Estelle] What's going on?
-Oh, hi, Mom. Uh, this is Sandy.

21:56.815 --> 21:58.066
That's Mindy's dad.

21:58.150 --> 21:59.860
-This is, uh, my mom.
-Nice to meet you.

21:59.943 --> 22:03.322
-Do you have any idea what time it is?
-I know exactly what time it is.

22:03.405 --> 22:05.324
So, what, you just don't care
about other people?

22:05.407 --> 22:08.201
You bang on doors and shoot your mouth off
while they're trying to sleep?

22:08.285 --> 22:09.786
I'm here to keep your son

22:09.870 --> 22:12.456
